column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Very Light Wind Blowing Cross Stream
column13:
Channel consists of gravel and sand with some cobbles and few boulders. Some sapplings and branches in the channel downstream of the bridge but appear to be affecting flow. Little to no vegetation in th channel. Bank vegetation at full growth - during higher water levels may cause a shift.
The gravel/sand bar just at the upstream side of the bridge appears to have washed out. The channel under the bridge is deep parabolic to triangular shaped then gradually shallows to a rectangular to parabolic shape at the typical metering section, ~10m dowstream of the bridge, and continues to the control.
Control is located ~ 70m downstream of gauging pool at a bend. Right side of the control/bend is infilled. At current water level the flow is diverted to the left of the channel. Logs/branches and debris caught up along the left bank at the bend just downstream of the control. Control consists of gravel and small cobbles. Currently stable but during high flows most likely will wash out and change. Completed control survey - see survey notes. Channel downstream of bridge is stable with vegetated banks. Channel bed /gravel upstream of the bridge is unstable during higher flows
column14: Section control. Uniform flow @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Gauging pool is along a bend on the right side of the channel, just upstream of the bridge. Gravel bar along the left side of the channel at the orifice confines flow to the right side (orifice side). Orifice was not burried. No reset. Mid-section
